In Liquid, you can include a hyphen in your tag syntax {% raw %}`{{-`, `-}}`, `{%-`, and `-%}`{% endraw %} to strip whitespace (including line breaks) from the left and/or right side of a rendered tag.

Normally, even if it doesn’t output text, any line of Liquid in your template will still output a blank line in your rendered HTML:

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% assign my_variable = "tomato" %}
{{ my_variable }}
{% endraw %}
```

Notice the blank line before “tomato” in the rendered template:

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">

tomato
</pre>

### Trim whitespace before

Using hyphen on opening tags ({% raw %}`{{-` and `{%-`{% endraw %}) will trim white space from content before the tag.

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
Start


My paragraph


{{- 'The end.' }}
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">
Start


My paragraph


{{- 'The end.' }}
</pre>

### Trim whitespace after

Using hyphen on closing tags ({% raw %}`-}}` and `-%}`{% endraw %}) will trim white space from content after the tag

#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{{ 'Start' -}}


My paragraph


The end.
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">
{{ 'Start' -}}


My paragraph

The end.
</pre>

### Trim whitespace before and after

Using hyphens on both opening and closing tags ({% raw %}`{{-`, `-}}`, `{%-`, and `-%}`{% endraw %}) will trim white space from both sides of the tag.


#### Input

```liquid
{% raw %}
{{ 'Start' -}}


My paragraph


{{- 'The end.' }}
{% endraw %}
```

#### Output

<pre class="raw-output">
{{ 'Start' -}}


My paragraph


{{- 'The end.' }}
</pre>

